Reference-contexts: When viewed in space-time the simulation algorithm above can be regarded as a feed-forward logical neural network, with threshold interaction and combining inputs using inclusive OR. Unfortunately this approach looks infeasible, because of links between coalescence-determination and the NP-complete SATISFIABILITY problem of computer science <ref> (Garey & Johnson, 1979, page 39) </ref>. However perhaps the intrinsic localization of the spatial birth-and-death process can come to the rescue here. Such questions place a premium on examining and inventing further varieties of coupling methods.
